rComments: Lectures are taken out almost directly out of the readings. There are about 100 pages to read every week and they are not about the most interesting things in political cultures. Took this class thinking it would be similar to another Politics class, but unfortunately it wasn't. Tests are relatively easy, if you do the readings. Overall, I wouldn't

Great professor.  This course introduced a number of facets composing us political culture.  Her teaching style engaged the class, and I was interested every week.  Readings are extensive but much needed.  This was her first time teaching 80G but she nailed it.
